      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Plans filed for the over-grading\nof crossings by the railroads show\nthat the new union depot will be\non Stevens and Front instead of on\nHoward, as was formerly supposed.\nStevens street will cut the struc-\nture in half. SIX through tracks\nwill run north of the depot and at\neither end four more tracks will\nbe laid. The viaducts over Post\nWall, Howard and Washington\nstreets will have clearance of IA\nfeet on an average and will carry\nten tracks."
    }
